parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine head gasket failure can cause oil leaks, engine overheating, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in costly repairs, accidents, or even fires.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the valve cover
engine overheating
engine failure
burning smell
fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause slow shifting, loss of gears, and difficulty shifting, which can lead to accidents, loss of vehicle control, and costly repairs.
symptoms: Slow shifting between gears
loss of reverse gear
transmission slipping
difficulty shifting
shifter wear
and malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission shifter failure can cause the vehicle to shift into neutral or other gears unintentionally, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Shifter made of plastic wears away
shifter malfunctions
vehicle shifts into neutral or other gears unintentionally
difficulty getting the vehicle out of park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle may roll or move unexpectedly when parked on an incline, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Difficulty shifting from park when parked on an incline
requiring the driver to start the engine and press the emergency brake
and then shift into park. The vehicle may roll backwards if the emergency brake is released without simultaneously shifting into park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle shaft can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud noise from the rear axle
broken rear axle shaft
cracked bracket holding the rear axle
and inability to drive the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the floor shift lever can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The floor shift lever will not lock when in park
causing the vehicle to roll backwards.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause the vehicle to lose stability, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: Rear end of the vehicle drops
noise coming from the rear suspension
rear sway bar or stabilizer bar failure
cracking or breaking of rear suspension components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt buckle can cause the seatbelt to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to unlatch, which can lead to entrapment or injury in the event of an accident or emergency situation.
symptoms: A piece of the seatbelt buckle breaks off
the seatbelt will not unlatch
the seatbelt becomes stuck
the "PRESS" button on the buckle is damaged.
